      children: "The New Chatbots Could Change the World. Can You Trust Them? Dec. 10, 2022 Welcome to the Age of Artificial Intelligence As A.I. systems continue to evolve and expand, so does their impact on our lives. After ChatGPT’s splashy debut, writing assistants have emerged to replace editors. Brian X. Chen, our tech columnist, put some of them to the test. Amid a boom in new tech tools, the University of Texas at Austin plans to offer a large-scale, low-cost online Master of Science degree program in artificial intelligence. The Turing test used to be the gold standard for proving machine intelligence. A new generation of bots is racing past it. Kevin Roose and Casey Newton talk to the cartoonist Sarah Andersen about why she and other artists are suing three companies that have developed A.I. image-generating tools. The website Character.AI allows visitors to chat with a reasonable facsimile of almost anyone, live or dead, real or (especially) imagined. We created our own artificial-technology system to understand how easy it is for a computer to generate fake faces. Do these people look real to you?"
