      children: "Every day in 2021 and the first quarter of 2022, I felt burned out. I could have blamed many things: the pandemic, a failed startup, or too much work. The root of the problem was... I was not taking care of my mental health."
    }), _jsx(_components.p, {
      children: "The Five Minute Journal changed my life"
    }), _jsx(_components.p, {
      children: "The first time I saw The Five Minute Journal by Intelligent Change in a Tim Ferris YouTube video titled How I Journal and Take Notes | Brainstorming + Focusing + Reducing Anxiety, I thought \"This is what I need. It will only take me five minutes. I can easily do this every morning\". And I did. Every day since April 2022."
    }), _jsx(_components.p, {
      children: "I ordered it from Amazon and received it in three days. On the first day, it took me more than fifteen minutes to fill out. I wasn't sure what to put in each section. I had to think about it for a moment. The next day it took me around three minutes. I got used to it quickly."
    }), _jsx(_components.p, {
      children: "Day by day, I felt better and better. I woke up more and more with a positive frame of mind. Within three weeks, that poisonous thought had disappeared. \"Not another day...\" did not cross my mind ever again. I woke up thinking \"Thank you for another day of life\"."
    }), _jsx(_components.p, {
      children: "The journal is pricey. Why should I buy it? You can pick a blank piece of paper and write every day. You could get a cheaper notebook. I think what makes The Five Minute Journal worth it is its simple structure, daily quotes and weekly challenges. It has pages to last for 6 months."
    }), _jsx(_components.p, {
      children: "The words you tell yourself every day If you wake up every day and tell yourself that you hate your current situation, it's an indication that you need to change it. Repeating your actions will reinforce what you think. Your thoughts will influence your actions and what you say to yourself. It is a feedback loop."
    }), _jsx(_components.p, {
